This paper is primarily focused on designing efficient ConvNets for mobile devices, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of neural architecture search (NAS) methods also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses hardware-aware design, which could fall under the neural engineering (cs.NE) or computer architecture (cs.AR) categories.
